<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4746744>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4. Compound microscope images showing detailed morphology for L. miyamotoi sp. nov., female specimen. (a) Dorsal habitus. (b) Ventral habitus. (c) Compound eye. (d) Head, ventral view. (e) Thorax, dorsal view. (f) Antenna and labium. (g) Thorax, ventral surface. (h) Thorax, with basal fore wing. (i) Metathoracic scent efferent system. (j) Protarsus. (k) Metatarsus. Abbreviations: AP, apodemal process; CX, coxa; EV, evaporative area; Ms: meso; Mt: meta; OS, ostiole; ST, sternum." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4746744/files/figure.png" .

